article_title: Tax clinics provide over $750 K in returns

og.description: Tax season is over and many might be celebrating the successes to help secure their finances over the next year. Three tax clinics were held at the Community Action Partnership of Western Nebraska to help those people who make $54,000 or less a year. Through the collaboration between two employees at Western Nebraska Community College and Community Action Partnership of Western Nebraska people were able to receive aid in filing their federal and state tax returns. Jennifer Sibal, alumni relations director at WNCC, and Carmen Trevino, family stabilization manager at CAPWN, wanted to assist people in the community with their taxes after a change in services offered by AARP volunteers changed this year.
